<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="201" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="201">
Afghanistan, Armenia, Azerbaijan, Georgia, Iran, Iraq, Jordan, Syria, Pakistan, Kazakhstan, Palestine, Tajikistan, Turkey, Turkmenistan and Uzbekistan: The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1842" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Capoeta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Capoeta" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Capoeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a wide distribution in the Mediterranean, Middle East, Caucasus and South-West Asia.
</paragraph>
